reviewText: Im a big Rodger Corman fan so these were a treat for me to see again. I really liked seeing "The Wasp Woman"again because I think its one of the best B-movies ever made

Sure, Corman's films were made fast and cheap.  But they're marvels.  Not all of them are good, but when they are - and this is a pretty good sampling - they're some of the weirdest psycho-sexual mind twists I've seen.  This set has terrible sound, making them hard to follow.  It's a shame because, really - there is content beyond the "wacky" plot outlines!  Still, this set is worth having around.
